**Primary**

RGB color value for Light Mode, separated by `,`.

By modifying this property, you can change the color value under Light Mode.

**Example**:
```css
/* Set Light Mode color value */
:root {
  --mdui-color-primary-light: 255, 0, 0;
}

/* Read Light Mode color value */
.element {
  color: rgb(var(--mdui-color-primary-light));
}

/* Read the color value that automatically adapts */
.element {
  color: rgb(var(--mdui-color-primary));
}

/* Read the color value that automatically adapts and add opacity */
.element {
  color: rgba(var(--mdui-color-primary), 0.5);
}
```

